    <name>Pro Tips: Self-Advocacy for Work &amp; Learning </name>
    <intro>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Pro%20Tip.png" alt="" width="140" height="136" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_middle" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use case studies in your instruction. ​&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;To introduce an instructional topic, adults will be&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;more&amp;nbsp;engaged by relevant situations (cases) they can&amp;nbsp;relate to, analyze (study) and then apply. As&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;real-life examples, case&amp;nbsp;studies increase relevance, value, and authenticity in learning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@1D59B5,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/relevance-value-authenticity" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@1D59B5,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 7.2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-scheme-color="@424242,," data-usefontface="true" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Include frequent and ongoing opportunities for self-reflection.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Adult learners are often already&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;juggling a career, family, and the daily demands of living. Classroom time can provide a space to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;offer new and necessary information, but it can also have built-in time for purposeful reflection. As&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;we’ve learned, reflection is critical for developing agency and assimilating new experiences. By&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;carving out time in class or dedicating time in a virtual setting for deliberate reflective activities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;(i.e., responding to relevant prompts or journaling practices) you can provide the adult learner&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;with necessary time to consolidate their experiences and get the most out of their educational&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;opportunity (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/self-regulation/self-assessment-reflection" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 9.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use UDL strategies to support planning and goal-setting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;It cannot be assumed that learners will&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;set appropriate goals to guide their work, but the answer should not be to provide goals for&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;students.&amp;nbsp;Such a short-term remedy does little to develop new skills or strategies in any&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;learner.&amp;nbsp;It is therefore important that learners develop the skill of effective goal setting.&amp;nbsp;The UDL&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;framework embeds graduated scaffolds for learning to set personal goals that are both&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;challenging and realistic (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Action &amp;amp; Expression&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression/executive-functions/strategy-development/strategy-development" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 6.2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/action-expression/executive-functions/goal-setting/goal-setting" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 6.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use UDL to create a safe learning environment.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;One of the most important things a teacher can&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;do is to create a safe space for learners.&amp;nbsp;To do this, teachers need to reduce potential threats and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;distractions in the learning environment.&amp;nbsp;When learners must focus their attention on having&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;basic needs met or avoiding negative experiences they cannot concentrate on the learning&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;process.&amp;nbsp;While the physical safety of a learning environment is of course necessary, subtler types&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;of threats and distractions must be attended to as well; what is threatening or potentially&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;distracting depends on learners’ individual needs and background (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank"&gt;Engagement&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Principle:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/threats-distractions" target="_blank"&gt;Checkpoint 7.3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider%20wave.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
